170 I find in Chapter 15 that Seven has ]n[ established that any of News, PBL ]^[ Foxtel (Sky Cable ]^[ Telstra Media) had the objective of destroying C7 ]^[ thereby substantially lessening competition. 
Seven has ]n[ demonstrated that any of those parties crossed the boundary that distinguishes legitimate, albeit aggressive ]^[ even ruthless competitive conduct from anti-competitive behaviour of the kind proscribed by ss 45(2) ]^[ 46(1) of the TP Act . 
171 In Chapter 16 , I conclude that Foxtel did ]n[ take advantage of its power in the retail pay television market in any of the ways alleged by Seven. 
172 In Chapter 17 , I reject Seven's case based on the conduct of Foxtel ]^[ Telstra Multimedia in denying C7 access to the Telstra Cable. 
I find that the requests made by C7 ]f[ retail access were intended to place pressure on Foxtel in relation to other issues. 
