352 Digital free-to-air television was introduced in Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth ]^[ Adelaide in 2001 ]^[ extended thereafter to regional areas. 
In compliance with their obligations, each of the Commercial Broadcasters ]^[ the National Broadcasters has delivered both SDTV ]^[ HDTV digital signals, at the same time as transmitting in analogue format. 
353 Although commercial broadcasting licensees are ]n[ permitted to ' multi-channel ' during a simulcast period, they are permitted to provide digital enhancements to their primary simulcast program, provided the enhancements are directly linked to, ]^[ contemporaneous with, that program. 
