2309 In my view, looking at the circumstances prevailing on 13 December 2000 ]v[ 25 January 2001, the very strong likelihood was that, in the absence of the conduct alleged to have contravened s 45(2)(b)(ii) of the TP Act , the major pay television retailers would have entered into an agreement on terms similar to those incorporated in the Foxtel-Optus CSA. 
