14.6.2.3 PREFERRED CONSTRUCTION 
2402 Since the particular question of construction I have identified is ]n[ concluded by authority, I must express my own view. 
This is no easy task, because the text of ss 45(2) ]^[ 4F of the TP Act is of even less assistance than usual in cases of statutory ambiguity. 
The fundamental reason ]f[ this is that, as Gummow J noted in News v South Sydney (in relation to s 4D), s 45(2) of the TP Act does ]n[ speak of human ]v[ corporate actions, ]b[ of the provision itself having the purpose of substantially lessening competition. 
