It is ]n[ surprising in these circumstances that s 4F does ]n[ clearly indicate whether it is directed to the position of a single corporation which has multiple purposes ]v[ to that of a number of corporations each of which has a different purpose ]v[ set of purposes. 
2403 McHugh J said in News v South Sydney 215 CLR, at 580 [42], that: 
'Questions of construction are notorious ]f[ generating opposing answers, none of which can be said to be either clearly right ]v[ clearly wrong. 
Frequently, there is simply no "right" answer to a question of construction'. 
