Nonetheless, on balance, I prefer a construction that limits the operation of s 45(2) to cases where the substantial purpose of each of the parties responsible ]f[ including the relevant provision in a contract is to substantially lessen competition. 
Several factors point to this conclusion. 
2404 First, if Seven's construction of ss 45(2) ]^[ 4F is correct, a party to a contract may be exposed ]n[ only to claims ]f[ damages ]^[ other relief, ]b[ to civil penalties under the TP Act because another party to the contract has included a provision ]f[ the ' substantial purpose ' of substantially lessening competition. 
