Mr Blomfield acted on instructions ]^[ did ]n[ determine whether News ]v[ its associated entities would become parties to the Master Agreement Provision. 
Foxtel Management is ]n[ alleged to have been a party to the Master Agreement. 
2584 My overall assessment of a very large amount of material is that News, through Mr Macourt ]^[ Mr Philip, thought that there were good commercial reasons ]f[ Foxtel to acquire the AFL pay television rights. 
A judgment was made that, in order to have a good chance of succeeding in a competitive auction ]f[ the AFL pay television rights, a bid of $30 million per annum would be required. 
The decision to support a bid at this price did ]n[ rest simply ]v[ even primarily on the results of modelling, ]b[ took account of other considerations, such as the ' strategic ' advantages of controlling the presentation of the AFL ]^[ avoiding the perceived problems of dealing with Seven as a free-to-air operator in charge of the rights. 
I do ]n[ regard the strategic advantages as having included the destruction of C7 as a specific objective, although both Mr Macourt ]^[ Mr Philip would have regarded that consequence with equanimity, if ]n[ enthusiasm, if it came about. 
2585 The models based on a rights fee of $30 million per annum were constructed ]f[ a variety of purposes. 
