3015 A third point, although I would have reached my conclusion in any event, is that I do ]n[ regard it as in the public interest that a party, especially an applicant in mega-litigation, should be able to insist on the Court resolving every factual issue it chooses to present, no matter how devoid of practical significance that issue may be. 
