(Emphasis in original. 
) 
3362 Brennan J explained (172 CLR, at 47) the result as follows: 
'In this case the [milk vendors] took no steps to hinder the acquisition by Jewel's customers of whatever goods Jewel had available ]f[ sale; the [milk vendors] simply failed to supply Jewel with New South Wales milk which Jewel could have supplied to the customers who sought it. 
