3364 In my opinion, the first ground rests on a distinction without a difference. 
It is hard to see why the ratio of Devenish v Jewel should be confined to the case where there is identity between the goods ]v[ services withheld from the target corporation (or which the target is prevented from acquiring) ]^[ the goods ]v[ services the target's customers are thereby prevented from acquiring. 
